 Restaurant Order & Menu Simulation System

📌 Project Description
The Restaurant Order & Menu Simulation System is a console-based application developed using Core Java. This system is designed to simulate real-world restaurant operations such as menu management, order processing, and billing.

The application follows Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles like encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism, and abstraction to ensure modular and maintainable code.# 🎯 Objectives
- To develop a menu-driven console application
- To manage restaurant menu items efficiently
- To allow customers to place orders easily
- To implement dynamic billing based on order types
- To demonstrate OOP concepts in real-world scenarios


 ⚙️ Features
👨‍💼 Admin Module
- Add new food items
- Update existing items
- Delete menu items
- View all menu items

 🧑‍🍳 Customer Module
- View menu
- Select food items
- Enter quantity
- Place multiple orders

💰 Billing System
- Dine-in → Service charge applied
- Takeaway → Packaging charge added
- Delivery → Distance-based charge (₹10/km)

 🧠 OOP Concepts Used
- Encapsulation → Data hiding using private variables
- Inheritance → Billing classes inherit from parent class
- Polymorphism → Different billing logic using method overriding
- Abstraction → Abstract class BillingService

 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Java (Core Java)
- Scanner Class (Input Handling)
- OOP Concepts

